Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 05 of Feet MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button
When I select 'Tendinopathy' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Localizer' is enabled

When I click on the Localizer
Then 'Extraarticular localization' canvas opens

When I select 'Tendon of M. peroneus brevis' on the canvas
And I close the canvas
Then 'Tendinopathy' checkbox is enabled
And 'Tear' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Tendinopathy' checkbox
Then 'T2w/PD hyperintensity' checkbox is enabled
And 'T1w hyperintensity' checkbox is enabled
And 'Thickening' checkbox is enabled
And 'Tendovaginitis' radio button is enabled
And 'Tendinitis' radio button is enabled
And 'Peritendinitis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hypervascularization of the tendon' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fluid in the common tendon sheath of the peroneal tendons' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fluid in the tendon sheath distal to the lateral malleolus' checkbox is enabled
And 'Os peroneum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Ganglion at the level of the insertion at Os metatarsal D1/Os cuboideum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Tendon dislocation' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Tendinitis' radio button
Then 'M. peroneus longus tendon' checkbox is enabled
